The reproductive system is diaulic (
Fig. 7D
). The preampullary duct widens into the narrow, elongate, and moderately short ampulla. The ampulla bifur- cates into the oviduct and the vas deferens. The vas deferens is quite long and convoluted, entering the wider proximal portion of the penial sac. The penial papilla is devoid of any armature. The somewhat rounded receptaculum seminis joins the oviduct and enters the female gland. The vagina opens ventrally to the penis.
